        <updateDate>2024-09-09T20:05:59Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Monetary Metals Tax Neutrality Act of 2024</strong></p><p>This bill exempts gains or losses from the sale or exchange of certain coins or bullion from recognition for income tax purposes. The exemption applies to gains or losses from the sale or exchange of (1) gold, silver, platinum, or palladium coins minted and issued by the Department of the Treasury; or (2) refined gold or silver bullion, coins, bars, rounds, or ingots that are valued primarily based on their metal content and not their form.&nbsp;</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
